---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { CONTACT_EMAIL, CINTURON_URL } from '../consts';
---

<Layout
  title="About"
  description="RePass Cloud Pty Ltd is an Australian engineering-led software firm that designs, builds, and operates enterprise-grade software platforms and cloud infrastructure tooling."
>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="hero-eyebrow">
        <i class="bi bi-building"></i>
        RePass Cloud Pty Ltd
      </div>
      <h1>Engineering-led software<br />built for production.</h1>
      <p class="hero-lead">
        We design, build, and operate enterprise-grade software platforms and cloud infrastructure
        tooling for organisations that need reliable technology in production environments.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">
          Work with us <i class="bi bi-arrow-right"></i>
        </a>
        <a href="/case-studies" class="btn btn-outline-light btn-lg">
          Case studies
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Who we are -->
  <section class="section bg-surface">
    <div class="container">
      <div style="max-width:760px; margin:0 auto;">
        <div class="section-label">Who we are</div>
        <h2>Not a generic consultancy</h2>
        <div style="color:var(--rpc-muted); line-height:1.8; font-size:1.05rem;">
          <p>
            RePass Cloud Pty Ltd is an Australian software engineering company and consultancy that
            designs, builds, and operates enterprise-grade software platforms, cloud infrastructure
            tooling, automation systems, and operational utilities for organisations that need
            practical, reliable technology built to run in real environments.
          </p>
          <p>
            We are not a generic software consultancy. We are an engineering-led organisation that
            builds serious operational software — from large multi-tenant SaaS platforms through to
            focused tools that solve specific, painful problems across cloud infrastructure, Windows
            environments, identity, reporting, file systems, and business operations.
          </p>
          <p>
            Our primary cloud focus is <strong>Microsoft Azure</strong> and <strong>AWS</strong>,
            with selective support for Google Cloud where required. Our delivery spans modern .NET
            platform development, PowerShell scripting and module development, Windows systems
            engineering, identity and access automation, and cloud-native design patterns.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Services -->
  <section class="section" id="services">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="text-center" style="margin-bottom:3rem;">
        <div class="section-label">What we do</div>
        <h2>Five capability areas</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="grid-3">
        <div class="feature-card">
          <div class="feature-icon"><i class="bi bi-cpu"></i></div>
          <h3>Enterprise Platform Development</h3>
          <p>Multi-tenant SaaS architecture, identity integration, tenant-aware configuration, audit logging, API-driven integrations, and commercial licensing models. Cinturon360 is the primary example.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-card">
          <div class="feature-icon"><i class="bi bi-cloud"></i></div>
          <h3>Cloud Infrastructure Tooling</h3>
          <p>Cloud cost and spend analysis, SSL certificate lifecycle management, cloud infrastructure automation, and Windows Golden VM automation across Azure and AWS.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-card">
          <div class="feature-icon"><i class="bi bi-gear-fill"></i></div>
          <h3>Business Operations & IT Tooling</h3>
          <p>ServiceNow ticket management, IT reporting automation, Windows machine performance tooling, fast delete utilities, SSH credential management, and AD identity automation.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-card">
          <div class="feature-icon"><i class="bi bi-microsoft"></i></div>
          <h3>Microsoft 365 & Identity Automation</h3>
          <p>User onboarding/offboarding triggered from HR changes, distribution list management, shared mailbox automation, identity lifecycle management, and cross-system integrations.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-card">
          <div class="feature-icon"><i class="bi bi-terminal"></i></div>
          <h3>PowerShell Automation & Scripting</h3>
          <p>Reusable PowerShell modules and enterprise scripts for Windows, Azure, Active Directory, Microsoft 365, and enterprise IT environments — maintained and distributable across organisations.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-card">
          <div class="feature-icon"><i class="bi bi-shield-check"></i></div>
          <h3>Security-first Engineering</h3>
          <p>Identity-centric access controls, least privilege design, strong separation of concerns, and auditability baked into every system from the ground up — not bolted on afterwards.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Cinturon360 -->
  <section class="section bg-surface" id="cinturon360">
    <div class="container">
      <div style="max-width:760px;">
        <div class="section-label">Flagship product</div>
        <h2>Cinturon360</h2>
        <p style="color:var(--rpc-muted); line-height:1.8; margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
          Cinturon360 is our actively developed and maintained enterprise SaaS platform. It is the
          operational control layer for organisations that need to manage complexity, customers,
          partners, and internal teams under structured governance without losing visibility or
          agility.
        </p>
        <p style="color:var(--rpc-muted); line-height:1.8; margin-bottom:2rem;">
          Cinturon360 is not just an automation tool. It is a platform for doing work in a
          controlled, auditable, and scalable way — one that grows with the organisation rather
          than becoming a source of technical debt.
        </p>
        <div style="display:flex; flex-wrap:wrap; gap:1.5rem; margin-bottom:2rem;">
          <div style="display:flex; align-items:flex-start; gap:0.75rem;">
            <i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill" style="color:var(--rpc-valid); margin-top:0.2rem;"></i>
            <span style="font-size:0.9rem;">Multi-tenant with strong isolation</span>
          </div>
          <div style="display:flex; align-items:flex-start; gap:0.75rem;">
            <i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill" style="color:var(--rpc-valid); margin-top:0.2rem;"></i>
            <span style="font-size:0.9rem;">Microsoft Entra ID integration</span>
          </div>
          <div style="display:flex; align-items:flex-start; gap:0.75rem;">
            <i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill" style="color:var(--rpc-valid); margin-top:0.2rem;"></i>
            <span style="font-size:0.9rem;">Full audit logging</span>
          </div>
          <div style="display:flex; align-items:flex-start; gap:0.75rem;">
            <i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill" style="color:var(--rpc-valid); margin-top:0.2rem;"></i>
            <span style="font-size:0.9rem;">Role-based permissions</span>
          </div>
          <div style="display:flex; align-items:flex-start; gap:0.75rem;">
            <i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill" style="color:var(--rpc-valid); margin-top:0.2rem;"></i>
            <span style="font-size:0.9rem;">Regional hosting flexibility</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <a href={CINTURON_URL} class="btn btn-primary" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
          Visit Cinturon360 <i class="bi bi-box-arrow-up-right"></i>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Technology stack -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-label">Technology focus</div>
      <h2 style="margin-bottom:1.5rem;">What we build with</h2>
      <div class="tech-stack" style="gap:0.75rem;">
        <span class="badge badge-secondary" style="padding:0.4em 0.9em; font-size:0.85rem;">.NET</span>
        <span class="badge badge-primary" style="padding:0.4em 0.9em; font-size:0.85rem;">Azure</span>
        <span class="badge badge-secondary" style="padding:0.4em 0.9em; font-size:0.85rem;">AWS</span>
        <span class="badge badge-secondary" style="padding:0.4em 0.9em; font-size:0.85rem;">Entra ID</span>
        <span class="badge badge-secondary" style="padding:0.4em 0.9em; font-size:0.85rem;">Active Directory</span>
        <span class="badge badge-secondary" style="padding:0.4em 0.9em; font-size:0.85rem;">Microsoft 365</span>
        <span class="badge badge-secondary" style="padding:0.4em 0.9em; font-size:0.85rem;">Windows Server</span>
        <span class="badge badge-secondary" style="padding:0.4em 0.9em; font-size:0.85rem;">PowerShell</span>
        <span class="badge badge-secondary" style="padding:0.4em 0.9em; font-size:0.85rem;">Hyper-V</span>
        <span class="badge badge-secondary" style="padding:0.4em 0.9em; font-size:0.85rem;">Google Cloud</span>
        <span class="badge badge-secondary" style="padding:0.4em 0.9em; font-size:0.85rem;">Docker</span>
        <span class="badge badge-secondary" style="padding:0.4em 0.9em; font-size:0.85rem;">WireGuard</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Principles -->
  <section class="section bg-surface">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="text-center" style="margin-bottom:3rem;">
        <div class="section-label">How we work</div>
        <h2>Our engineering principles</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="grid-3">
        <div class="principle-card">
          <div class="principle-icon"><i class="bi bi-shield-lock-fill"></i></div>
          <div class="principle-title">Security-first by design</div>
          <div class="principle-desc">Every system we build is architected with security and compliance requirements from day one, not bolted on afterwards.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="principle-card">
          <div class="principle-icon"><i class="bi bi-gear-fill"></i></div>
          <div class="principle-title">Engineering-led, not sales-led</div>
          <div class="principle-desc">We focus on getting the implementation right. Our products exist because we saw problems in the market and built tools to fix them.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="principle-card">
          <div class="principle-icon"><i class="bi bi-arrow-repeat"></i></div>
          <div class="principle-title">Automation over manual process</div>
          <div class="principle-desc">If a human is doing something a machine can do reliably, we automate it. That frees people to do the work that actually matters.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="principle-card">
          <div class="principle-icon"><i class="bi bi-cpu"></i></div>
          <div class="principle-title">Production-proven</div>
          <div class="principle-desc">We build for real environments with real load, compliance requirements, and audit obligations. Everything is designed to run in production.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="principle-card">
          <div class="principle-icon"><i class="bi bi-file-earmark-check"></i></div>
          <div class="principle-title">Compliance &amp; audit-ready</div>
          <div class="principle-desc">Governance, access control, audit logging, and evidence trails are built in — not an afterthought.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="principle-card">
          <div class="principle-icon"><i class="bi bi-geo-alt-fill"></i></div>
          <div class="principle-title">Built in Australia</div>
          <div class="principle-desc">Our team, our infrastructure, and our support are Australian. Data sovereignty and local compliance requirements are things we understand.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA banner -->
  <section class="cta-banner">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-label" style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.5);">Work with us</div>
      <h2>Let's build something together.</h2>
      <p>
        We work with organisations that need enterprise software, cloud automation, or operational
        tooling built properly — not quickly patched, not over-engineered.
      </p>
      <div class="cta-actions">
        <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">
          Get in touch <i class="bi bi-arrow-right"></i>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
